account of Schaller's time in this little-known and remote country, where he studied and helped develop conservation initiatives for the snow leopard, Gobi bear, wild camel, and Mongolian gazelle, among other species. Featuring magnificent photographs from his travels, the book offers a critical, at times inspiring contribution for those who treasure wildlife, as well as a fresh perspective on the natural beauty of the region, which encompasses steppes, mountains, and the Gobi Desert.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNatural historyzMongolia. 0aWildlife conservationzMongolia. 0aWildlife habitat improvementzMongolia. 0aWildlife managementzMongolia. 7aNATURE / Ecosystems & Habitats / Mountains.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishz978311070475408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069231040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300252729?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300252729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300252729/original  a978-3-11-069231-0  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070475-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPCb2020